   The 50-year-old son of Art Linkletter was en route from Gualala,
about 100 miles north of San Francisco, to John Wayne Airport in
Orange County on Thursday when the engine on his Cessna 206
six-seater lost oil pressure and threw a rod, forcing the landing.
   The plane landed in a grassy field near the university, about 30
miles north of San Francisco. Linkletter was unhurt.
   Linkletter splits his time between Gualala, where he handles
investments for his family's string of enterprises, and Laguna
Beach, where he is a developer.
