<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Ethiopia-Prisoners     09-02 0152</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Ethiopia-Prisoners,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>Emperor's Grandsons Among Freed Prisoners</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ADDIS ABABA, Ethiopia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three grandsons of the late Emperor
Haile Selassie were among 87 political prisoners released Saturday
to mark the anniversary of the revolution that toppled their
grandfather 15 years ago.
   The three, all children of the late emperor's son, Makonnen Haile
Selassie, had been in prison since the revolution, officials said.
   The three grandsons are Wossen-Segid Makonnen and his brothers
Michael and Beide-Mariam.
   They were ordered freed with the other prisoners to mark the
Ethiopian New Year and the anniversary of the revolution.
   Ethiopia, which uses the Julian calendar, marks its new year on
Sept. 11. Revolution Day will be celebrated the following day.
   Also released Saturday was Zegeye Asfaw, who served as justice
minister under the provisional military government that overthrew
the emperor.
   About 820 common criminals were also released from jails
throughout the country to mark the anniversaries.
