<HEAD>Dozens Injured at Concert</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBUQUE, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Young women tossed panties and bras on stage
and crowds toppled barriers, injuring dozens of spectators, during a
pop concert by soap opera heartthrob Michael Damian, authorities
said.
   There were no serious injuries and no arrests in the incident
Friday night at the Dubuque County Fairgrounds, the Dubuque
sheriff's office said.
   Ambulance crews examined or treated about 40 people at the scene
for minor injuries and heat-related problems, and another 24 people
were treated at a hospital and released, police said.
   The sheriff's office said no special security arrangements had
been made for the event featuring Damian, a star of the TV soap
opera ``The Young and the Restless'' and a pop singer.
   The crowd of 3,500 to 4,000 was unexpectedly large, and made up
mostly of teen-age girls and young women, police said.
   Some people were pushed against crowd-control barriers or stepped
on when the crowd surged toward the stage. Sheriff's officers and
state troopers helped restore order.
   ``They were throwing panties and bras up on the stage,'' said a
police dispatcher, who would not give her name.
