<FIRST>r i AM-Israel-Uprising     09-02 0368</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Israel-Uprising,0379</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Suspected Collaborators Killed; Widespread Unrest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARJORIE OLSTER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Arab militants stabbed to death three
Palestinians they accused of collaborating with Israel, and Israeli
troops shot and wounded 21 Arabs in the occupied territories, Arab
reports said Friday.
   An army spokeswoman confirmed the three deaths, but said one of
the victims was a drug dealer killed in a dispute with other
criminals.
   She said a second victim was a Palestinian inmate of Ketsiot
prison in southern Israel who was stabbed to death by another
prisoner during a riot Thursday night. Police are investigating the
circumstances, she said.
   Arab reporters identified the man as Jamal Othman Khalaf, 25, of
Gaza city. Khalaf was serving a 2{-year sentence for allegedly
carrying out directives of underground leaders of the Palestinian
uprising.
   Khalaf was the 11th Ketsiot inmate killed by fellow Palestinians
since the uprising began in December 1987. Arab reports said he was
suspected of collaborating with Israel's Shin Bet secret police.
   In the West Bank village of Keffin the body of Muhammed Herscheh,
45, was found with multiple stab wounds. Arab reports said the Shin
Bet had given Herscheh a gun for self defense.
   Masked youths in the southern Gaza Strip town of Rafah attacked
Muhammed Nasser Bul Bul, 38, with knives and axes as he was leaving
a mosque after Friday afternoon Moslem prayers, Arab and army
reports said. He died of his wounds later in the hospital, doctors
reported.
   Palestinians said Bul Bul was a ollaborator who received land
from Israel.
   The army spokeswoman denied the report and said the dead man was
a drug dealer killed by fellow criminals.
   A youth from Keffin was among four Palestinians shot and wounded
by troops Friday in the occupied West Bank.
   At least 17 Palestiniand were wounded in clashes with troops in
the Gaza Strip, Arab reports said. The army did not confirm any of
the casualties.
   The deaths bring the toll to 103 Palestinians killed by fellow
Arabs, most of them as suspected collaborators, since the uprising
against Israeli rule began in 1987. Troops and Jewish settlers have
killed 554 Palestinians and Arabs have killed 39 Jews in the
violence.
</TEXT>
